property.name: description
property.value:
If EP - Targeted Ablation Substrate was:
"Accessory pathway - concealed", then Outcome of Ablation selections are: - Elimination of retrograde AP conduction - Persistence of retrograde conduction, without SVT - Persistence of retrograde conduction, with SVT - Unknown or Ambiguous
"Accessory pathway - manifest (bidirectional WPW)", then Outcome of Ablation selections are: - Elimination of antegrade conduction (Elimination of retrograde conduction) - Elimination of antegrade conduction (Persistence of retrograde conduction, with SVT) - Elimination of antegrade conduction (Persistence of retrograde conduction, without SVT) - Persistence of antegrade conduction (Elimination of retrograde conduction, with SVT) - Persistence of antegrade conduction (Elimination of retrograde conduction, without SVT) - Persistence of antegrade conduction (Persistence of retrograde conduction, with SVT) - Persistence of antegrade conduction (Persistence of retrograde conduction, without SVT) - Unknown or Ambiguous
"Accesory pathway manifest (antegrade only WPW)", then Outcome of Ablation selections are: - Elimination of antegrade AP conduction - Persistence of antegrade conduction, without SVT - Persistence of antegrade conduction, with SVT - Unknown or Ambiguous
"Accessory pathway - manifest (unidirectional anterograde decremental pathway - Mahaim)", then Outcome of Ablation selections are: - Elimination of antegrade AP conduction - Persistence of antegrade conduction, without SVT O Persistence of antegrade conduction, with SVT - Unknown or Ambiguous
"AV node", then Outcome of Ablation selections are: - Ablation ineffective - Attenuation of AV conduction - Elimination of AV conduction - Unknown or Ambiguous
"AV node (fast pathway)", then Outcome of Ablation selections are: - Elimination of fast pathway conduction (Attenuation of AV conduction) - Elimination of fast pathway conduction (Elimination of AV conduction) - Elimination of fast pathway conduction (No change in AV conduction) - Persistence of fast pathway conduction (Attenuation of AV conduction) - Persistence of fast pathway conduction (Elimination of AV conduction) - Persistence of fast pathway conduction (No change in AV conduction) - Unknown or Ambiguous
"AV node (slow pathway)", then Outcome of Ablation selections are: - Elimination of slow pathway conduction - Persistence of slow pathway conduction (Persistence of spontaneous or inducible SVT) - Persistence of slow pathway conduction (with single echoes but no SVT) - Persistence of slow pathway conduction (without echoes) - Unknown or Ambiguous
"His bundle", then Outcome of Ablation selections are: - Elimination of ectopic focus/tachycardia (Attenuation of AV conduction) - Elimination of ectopic focus/tachycardia (Elimination of AV conduction) - Elimination of ectopic focus/tachycardia (No change in AV conduction) - Persistence of ectopic focus/tachycardia (Attenuation of AV conduction) - Persistence of ectopic focus/tachycardia (Elimination of AV conduction) - Persistence of fast pathway conduction (No change in AV conduction) - Unknown or Ambiguous
"Myocardium - atrial", then Outcome of Ablation selections are: - Substrate eliminated - Substrate attenuated - Ablation ineffective - Unknown or Ambiguous
"Myocardium - coronary sinus", then Outcome of Ablation selections are: - Substrate eliminated - Substrate attenuated - Ablation ineffective - Unknown or Ambiguous
"Myocardium-ventricular", then Outcome of Ablation selections are: - Elimination of spontaneous/inducible VT - Persistence of spontaneous/inducible VT (with non- sustained VT) - Persistence of spontaneous/inducible VT (with sustained VT) - Unknown or Ambiguous
"Sinus node", then Outcome of Ablation selections are: - Normalization of sinus node function - Persistent inappropriate sinus tachycardia - Sinus bradycardia or arrest - Unknown or Ambiguous
